HEADWORD: Infaust
<hw>In*faust"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>infaustus</ets>; pref. <ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>faustus</ets>
fortunate, lucky.]</ety> <def>Not favorable; unlucky; unpropitious;
sinister.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Ld. Lytton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

